_source.businessDescription: Albedo Limited, an investment holding company, engges in the supply and distribution of industrial and engineering raw materials to the metals industry Singapore and internationally. The company’s Trading and Distribution segment offers raw materials, including steel rolls and ferro alloys; and provides customer services. Its Resources Trading segment is involved in the trade of minerals, resources, and bulk commodities, which include iron ore, pig iron, manganese ore, thermal coal, coking coal, ferrous and non-ferrous scrap, and semi-finished and finished steel. The company’s products also include consumables and disposable supplies, measuring systems, equipment and engineering spares for steelmaking plants, steel rolling mills, cast iron, steel foundries, silicon manganese, nitrovanadium, aluminium, copper, nickel, recarburizer, thermocouples, and analyzing probes. Albedo Limited was founded in 2005 and is based in Singapore.
_source.companyAddress: 1 Scotts Road, No 20-03/04 Shaw Centre, Singapore  228208, Singapore

_source.businessDescription: Addvalue Technologies Ltd, an investment holding company, provides satellite-based communication terminals and solutions for various voice and IP-based data applications in Asia, Europe, and North America. The company develops and manufactures a range of terminals operating on satellite networks for land, maritime, and aeronautical applications; and designs and supplies customized solutions for tracking, telemetry, supervisory control and data acquisition, GSM backhauling, and VSAT backup. It also designs, develops, and distributes telecommunications equipment and related products; and provides design services, including initial product conceptualisation, development and evaluation, qualification and regulatory approval, field trial, pilot run, and mass production. The company markets its products and solutions under the Wideye brand. Addvalue Technologies Ltd was founded in 1994 and is based in Singapore.
_source.companyAddress: 28 Tai Seng Street, No. 06-02, Singapore  534106, Singapore

_source.businessDescription: Asia Enterprises Holding Limited, an investment holding company, engages in procuring, distributing, and trading steel products to industrial end-users. Its products include shipbuilding plates/high tensile plates, hot-rolled steel plates/chequered steel plates, wide-flanged beams, bulb flats, channels, equal angles/unequal angles/inverted angles, round/square flat bars, hollow sections, seamless/ERW API grade pipes, and serrated galvanized gratings. The company also processes and supplies steel materials, such as cold-rolled, electro-galvanized, hot-dipped galvanized, stainless, and hot rolled pickled and oiled coils/sheets. It supplies approximately 1,200 steel products to customers involved primarily in marine and offshore, oil and gas, and construction, as well as in the precision metal stamping, manufacturing, and engineering/fabrication industries in Singapore, Indonesia, Malaysia, and other Asia Pacific markets. The company was founded in 1961 and is based in Singapore.

AP Oil International Limited manufactures and sells various lubricating oils and fluids, and specialty chemicals. It operates in three segments: Manufacturing, Trading, and Franchising. The company’s products consist of automotive lubricants that include gasoline and gas engine oils, diesel engine oils, motorcycle engine oils, and specialty lubricants and fluids, as well as industrial lubricants, such as chain, compressor, gear, gas engine, heat transfer, and paper machine oil; hydraulic fluid; pneumatic tool lubricant; and slideway, textile, transformer, turbine, and white oil. Its products also include neat and water soluble cutting oils; and rust preventive, stamping, and forming fluids, as well as marine lubricants, grease, and industrial special oils and fluids. In addition, the company engages in trading base oil, additives, and specialty chemicals. It sells its products under AP Oil and SINO brand names. AP Oil International Limited markets its products in Singapore, Indonesia, Malaysia, Thailand, Vietnam, Myanmar, Cambodia, the Philippines, Bangladesh, Nepal, China, Taiwan, Hong Kong, Japan, Fiji, and the Middle East. The company was formerly known as Huan Chew Oil Trading Pte Ltd. AP Oil International Limited was founded in 1975 and is based in Singapore.

Ascott Residence Trust operates as a real estate investment trust in Singapore. It invests in real estate and real estate-related assets, which are used as serviced residences or rental housing properties in the Asia-Pacific region. As of December 31, 2006, Ascott Residence’s property portfolio comprised 2,304 serviced residence units in 14 properties located in Singapore, China, Indonesia, Japan, the Philippines, and Vietnam. The company was founded in 2006 and is based in Singapore, Singapore.
_source.companyAddress: 168 Robinson Road, #30-01 Capital Tower, Singapore    Singapore

_source.businessDescription: Chu Kong Shipping Enterprises (Group) Company Limited, an investment holding company, primarily offers cargo transportation services in Hong Kong and the People's Republic of China. It engages in shipping agency and freight forwarding; river trade cargo direct shipment and transshipment; container transportation, handling, repair, and towing; trucking businesses; and wharf cargo handling, cargo consolidation, and godown storage activities. The company also offers passenger transportation agency and carrier services, as well as is involved in the travel agency operation. In addition, it engages in the management of ships; provision of logistics services; provision of advertising services; operation and management of marine cargo terminal; tour operations; and property holding activities. The company was formerly known as Chu Kong Shipping Development Company Limited and changed its name to Chu Kong Shipping Enterprises (Group) Company Limited in June 2012. Chu Kong Shipping Enterprises (Group) Company Limited was founded in 1996. The company is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong, and is considered a Red Chip company due to its listing on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange. Chu Kong Shipping Enterprises (Group) Company Limited is a subsidiary of Chu Kong Shipping Enterprises (Holdings) Company Limited.

_source.businessDescription: CNA Group Ltd. engages in the provision, design, and implementation of integrated control and automation systems, and IT solutions for buildings and facilities. It operates in three segments: Mechanical, Electrical and Plumbing; Information Communication Technology; and Maintenance, Sales of Products and Others. The company undertakes mechanical, electrical, and plumbing works related to infrastructural projects, such as hospitals, airports, commercial buildings etc. It also offers information communication technology products, including ELV systems, intelligent building management systems, and energy management systems, which are installed to automate, control, and manage virtually every facility in buildings or industrial plants. In addition, the company maintains control and automation solutions in airports, water treatment facilities, and commercial buildings; and sells indoor air quality solution products, such as filtration systems and germicidal UVC emitters that are used in hospitals and offices, as well as provides after-sales, maintenance, and facility management services. The company primarily operates in Singapore, the People’s Republic of China, the Middle East, Vietnam, Thailand, the Philippines, Malaysia, India, and Australia. CNA Group Ltd. was incorporated in 1990 and is based in Singapore.
_source.companyAddress: 28 Kaki Bukit Crescent, Kaki Bukit Techpark 1, Singapore  416259, Singapore

_source.businessDescription: BH Global Corporation engages in the wholesale and retail of electrical goods, appliances, and related products in marine supply and servicing industry worldwide. The company is also involved in the wholesale trade of marine equipment and accessories; assembly, manufacture, and repair of switchboards and switch gears for vessels; manufacture and supply of specialty steel wires and other wires; provision of marine and offshore related products and services; and securing and installing facilities for the marine and offshore sectors, as well as offers turnkey electrical and instrumentation installation services. Its marine cables and accessories include offshore, FPSO, marine shipboard, marine data communication, and industrial cables; cable glands, junction boxes, and shrouds; heat shrinkable products; cable joints and terminations; cable ties, straps, and identification markers; cable markers; transit sealing systems; cable cleats and lugs; and multi-cable transits and cable support systems. The company’s hazardous areas zone rated electrical products comprise fire safety alarms and beacons; lightings for hazardous locations; explosion proof electrical equipment; offshore helideck lightings and wind sock assemblies; plugs and receptacles; rechargeable flashlights for hazardous locations; and various electrical products. Its maritime equipment and electrical supplies consist of lighting fixtures and luminaries; maritime electrical installation products; wiring devices; enclosures; ship automation and electrical distribution products; maritime electrical products; marine DC power supply systems; fire safety alarms beacon; lamps and lighting components; marine whistles, and navigation and signaling lights; and plugs and receptacles. The company was formerly known as BH Global Marine Limited and changed its name to BH Global Corporation in May 2013. The company is headquartered in Singapore. BH Global Corporation is a subsidiary of Beng Hui Holding (S) Pte. Ltd.

Biosensors International Group, Ltd., an investment holding company, engages in the research and development, manufacture, assembly, marketing, distribution, and sale of medical devices for interventional cardiology and critical care procedures worldwide. It operates through three segments: Interventional Cardiology, Critical Care, and Licensing Revenue. The Interventional Cardiology segment supplies its proprietary drug-eluting stent products, coronary bare-metal stents, accompanying stent delivery balloon catheter systems, angioplasty balloons, and catheters under the BioMatrix Flex, BioMatrix NeoFlex, Axxess, BioFreedom, Gazelle, and Powerline brand names. The Critical Care segment supplies catheter systems and related accessories that are used in surgeries, and intensive care treatment and monitoring procedures. It offers its products under the ACCUTRANS, BIOTRANS, and BIOTRAY brand names. The Licensing Revenue segment engages in the licensing of its proprietary drug-eluting stent technology and intellectual property. The company was founded in 1990 and is headquartered in Singapore.
_source.companyAddress: Kaki Bukit Avenue 1, Block 10, No. 06-01/04, Singapore  417942, Singapore

_source.businessDescription: Cacola Furniture International Limited, an investment holding company, is engaged in the design, manufacture, sale, marketing, distribution, and retail of a range of home and office furniture primarily in the People’s Republic of China. The company offers various panel furniture products, such as display cabinets, shelves, tables, and chairs for the living room; beds, chests of drawers, wardrobes, nightstands, armories, and children’s furniture for the bedroom; dining tables, chairs, sideboards, and cabinets for the dining room; and writing desks, bookcases, and computer units for office. It also provides fabric and leather sofas, which comprise a set of a one-seater, two-seater, and three-seater sofas, as well as a set of two one-seater and a three-seater sofas; and mattresses. The company also sells its products in the Unites States, Canada, Spain, South Africa, and internationally. Cacola Furniture International Limited was founded in 1999 and is headquartered in Dongguan, the People’s Republic of China.
_source.companyAddress: Changlang Avenue, Changping Town, Dongguan, Guangdong Province, 523577, China
